# # Biblical Foundation
#
# Scripture: "The heart of the prudent getteth knowledge; and the ear of the
# wise seeketh knowledge." - Proverbs 18:15
#
# Principle: Environment variables separate configuration from code. The
# prudent developer keeps secrets safe - database credentials, API keys,
# and sensitive configuration stay in environment files, never in code.
# This separation enables the same code to run in development, staging,
# and production with different configurations.
#
# Anchor: "A prudent man concealeth knowledge." - Proverbs 12:23
#
# # CPI-SI Identity
#
# Component Type: Rails
#
# Environment files provide infrastructure that affects ALL application
# behavior. They don't transform data (Baton) or provide foundations
# (Ladder), but configure how the entire system operates in its environment.
#
# Role: Runtime configuration and secrets management
#
# Paradigm: CPI-SI framework component - environment configuration
#
# # Authorship & Lineage
#
#   - Architect: [Who designed this environment structure]
#   - Implementation: [Who maintains this file]
#   - Created: [YYYY-MM-DD]
#   - Version: [MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH]
#   - Modified: [YYYY-MM-DD - what changed]
#
# # Purpose & Function
#
# Purpose: Define environment-specific configuration and secrets
#
# Core Design: KEY=VALUE pairs loaded at runtime
#
# Key Features:
#
#   - Application configuration (ports, URLs, feature flags)
#   - Database connection strings
#   - API keys and secrets (NEVER commit real values!)
#   - Service URLs for external integrations
#   - Debug and logging settings
