#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Validation
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Verify environment variables are loaded:
#
#   # Node.js
#   require('dotenv').config()
#   console.log(process.env.APP_NAME)
#
#   # Python
#   from dotenv import load_dotenv
#   load_dotenv()
#   print(os.getenv('APP_NAME'))
#
#   # Go
#   godotenv.Load()
#   os.Getenv("APP_NAME")
#
#   # Shell
#   source .env && echo $APP_NAME
#
# Common Issues:
#
#   "Variable undefined" - Check file is loaded, no typos in key name
#   "Wrong value" - Check loading order, system env may override
#   "Quotes in value" - Some loaders include quotes literally
#   "Spaces break value" - Use quotes: KEY="value with spaces"
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security Checklist
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Before committing or deploying:
#
#   ✅ .env is in .gitignore
#   ✅ .env.example has placeholder values only
#   ✅ Real secrets are NEVER in git history
#   ✅ Production secrets use secure secrets manager
#   ✅ API keys are scoped to minimum required permissions
#   ✅ Secrets are rotated periodically
#
# If secrets were accidentally committed:
#   1. Rotate ALL exposed credentials immediately
#   2. Use git filter-branch or BFG to remove from history
#   3. Force push (coordinate with team)
#   4. Review access logs for unauthorized use
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Modification Policy
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Safe to Modify:
#   ✅ Add new environment variables
#   ✅ Change default development values
#   ✅ Add comments explaining variables
#   ✅ Reorganize sections for clarity
#
# Modify with Care:
#   ⚠️ Changing variable names (breaks code references)
#   ⚠️ Removing variables (may break dependent code)
#   ⚠️ Changing production defaults
#
# NEVER:
#   ❌ Commit real secrets, API keys, or passwords
#   ❌ Use weak/guessable secret values in production
#   ❌ Share .env files via insecure channels
#   ❌ Log environment variables in production
#   ❌ Remove 4-block documentation structure
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Creating .env.example
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# For team sharing, create .env.example with placeholder values:
#
#   # Replace this:
#   DB_PASSWORD=real_password_here
#
#   # With this in .env.example:
#   DB_PASSWORD=[your-database-password]
#
# The .env.example file IS committed to version control.
# New developers copy it to .env and fill in real values.
